cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about object segmentation using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model for weakly supervised segmentation, which involves learning from image-level labels rather than pixel-level labels. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to the development of machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on a segmentation benchmark, which involves comparing the performance of different algorithms on a specific dataset. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
